An early start waited on Saturday, 18 June, for participants taking part in the second annual Soutpansberg Mountain Marathon as part of the Mountain Marathon Series, hosted by KZN Trail Running. Hosted in conjunction with the Endangered Wildlife Trust (EWT), the event started and finished at the Schoemansdal Environmental Education Centre. This year’s top three finishers in the 40km mountain marathon event were Cornelius Rall in first place, Gary Calitz in second and Jeofrey Mashau third. The first woman home was Christili Muller, followed by Chana-Lee Preston and Jolanda Roux third. As for the mountain challenge event over 23km, first to cross the finish line was Hennie Niekerk, with Tharollo Mthisi second and Khathutshelo Mukhumeni third. The first lady home was Debbie Blount, followed by Nancy Barber and Dawn Booyens. For full results, including those of the medium (10km) and short (5km) events, visit https://mountainmarathonseries.com/results/